SIMPLE: kneecap
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: kneecap
<hw>knee"cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A roundish, flattened, sesamoid bone in the
tendon in front of the knee joint; the patella; the kneepan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cap or protection for the knee.</def></p>

<p><ent>kneecap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: kneecap
<hw>knee"cap</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>to break the knees of,
especially by shooting in the kneecap; -- often done by criminal or
terrorist groups as a warning or punishment.</def> <note></note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> knee-cap.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knee-crooking</ent>⟦br⟧
